<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-10-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="919" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d919">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Meyer</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-10-20"><hi rend="italic">October 20,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>At request of Japanese Government you will, upon consent being given by
                            Russia, continue your friendly offices in behalf of Japanese Government
                            and subjects pending the reestablishment of the Japanese legation, and
                            will instruct our consuls to same effect by telegraph.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>